'''William R. "Bill" Rhodes''' is President and [[Chief Executive Officer|CEO]] of William R. Rhodes Global Advisors, LLC, and professor-at-large at [[Brown University]]. He is also a senior adviser for [[Citi]], having stepped back from full-time responsibilities after more than 53 years. He is the retired Senior Vice Chairman and Senior International Officer of [[Citigroup]] and [[Citibank]], whom he joined in 1957.

As of May 2007 he was among the Board of the [[Americas Society]] affiliate, the [[Council of the Americas]], which was originally founded by [[David Rockefeller]] in 1965.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://207.21.242.176/coa/about/boardofdir.html |title=Council of the Americas website: Board of Directors |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20070529005621/http://207.21.242.176/coa/about/boardofdir.html |archivedate=May 29, 2007}}</ref>

In 2011, [[McGraw-Hill]] published his book ''Banker to the World: Leadership Lessons From the Front Lines of Global Finance''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.foreignaffairs.com/articles/68150/william-rhodes/banker-to-the-world-leadership-lessons-from-the-front-lines-of-g|title=Banker to the World: Leadership Lessons From the Front Lines of Global Finance|last=Cooper|first=Richard N.|date=September/October 2011|work=Foreign Affairs|accessdate=26 June 2012}}</ref>

